d_1.head: Internet Disconnect
d_1.summary: Mrs. Hughes calls to disconnect her internet service. She wants to switch to another provider. Hear how this retention agent attempts to make the save!
d_1.subhead: Mrs. Hughes calls to disconnect her internet service. She wants to switch to another provider. Hear how this retention agent attempts to make the save!

events.agent: Thank you for calling Cox. My name is Jayden.
How can I help you today?
events.customer: I'd like to cancel my internet service, please.

events.agent: I can assist you with that; give me a moment to pull up your account. Mrs. Hughes, I see you've had TV and Internet with us since 2010. Can I ask you a few questions?
events.customer: Okay but I'm in a hurry; I just want to get this done.

events.agent: Okay I can get that going; how's the service been in general?
events.customer: Fine, I guess; I'm planning to switch to another provider with faster internet speeds.

events.agent: I understand; looking at your account I see you've had the same Internet plan for a few years now. Let me ask, how many people in your household use the internet?
events.customer: My husband and I myself.

events.agent: What types of things do you do online?
events.customer: I work from home so I need a fairly fast internet connection here. And we just bought a media streaming device.

events.agent: Those are really convenient, aren't they? Did you know you can get access to a lot of great on-demand content with Apps that work with your existing Cox TV service?
events.customer: Yeah I've been looking into that.

events.agent: I use the AMC app a lot to watch past episodes my favorite shows. Let me see what we have here... there are several promotions available in your area that will give you faster internet so you can take full advantage of your streaming device.
events.customer: Is it different than what's on the website? Because I checked already and everything was more expensive than I'm willing to pay.

events.agent: Let's have a closer look. You mentioned you work from home; I bet that means lots of conference calls and phone time, right?
events.customer: Yes; on some days.

events.agent: We have a promotion on our Bronze Bundle with Phone. It's only ten dollars more than what you're currently paying.
events.customer: Well I don't need home phone because I use my cell for everything.

events.agent: I understand; let me give you a few more details... with this bundle we can upgrade your internet speed to 100 mega bits per second, which is 10 times faster than what you currently have. How does that sound?
events.customer: Pretty good; but do I still need to get home phone? Can't I get just the internet upgraded?

events.agent: I can do that; however, this bundle gives you much more value for your dollar. Do you make many long distance calls?
events.customer: Yes, I do

events.agent: Here's what great with this bundle: we can offer you unlimited long distance nationwide and to Canada and Mexico. Customers tell me they still prefer the quality and reliability of a landline over cellular.
events.customer: Okay; just so I understand, you're saying with this bundle I get home phone with unlimited long distance, my existing digital TV, and faster internet... how much would I be paying?

events.agent: Let me get the exact figure... your monthly bill would be _. And I can lock in this great price for 12 months. What do you think?
events.customer: Hmmm; I just don't need or want a landline...

events.agent: I can upgrade your internet alone but chances are you'll be paying around the same price or more but with fewer services. I can look into this if you like.
events.customer: No thanks. I'll go elsewhere for faster internet.

events.agent: I'm sorry to hear that; you've been a loyal customer for many years and we really want to keep your business. Would you mind if I put you on hold for a moment while I look into some additional options?
events.customer: I guess so but I really need to get going.

events.agent: Thanks for your patience, Mrs. Hughes. I spoke with my supervisor. I'm able upgrade your internet to Cox Preferred 100 at a special rate for the next 6 months. Your monthly bill will be about the same and you'll get the faster internet.
Would you like me to set that up for you?
events.customer: Before you do that, what happens after six months?

events.agent: The service will go back to regular price; but, we're always running new promotions so why not take advantage of the savings by keeping your internet service with us? I see you already have a modem in your home that supports the faster speed; so, I can upgrade your internet without a technician needing to visit.
events.customer: Well, that would save me the hassle of changing.

events.agent: May I process the changes to your account so you can start taking advantage of a faster internet connection immediately?
events.customer: Yeah; let's to it.

events.agent: Great; please stay on the line while I make these changes.
events.customer: Okay; thanks.

events.agent: Alright; you're all set. Is there anything else I can help you with today?
events.customer: No. Thanks for your help.

events.agent: It's my pleasure. Thanks for choosing Cox. Have a great day!
events.customer: You too; good bye.
